data.title: Artest Has New Name, New Perspective on Time with Pacers
data.meta_description: The Lakers' practice on the Bankers Life Fieldhouse practice court had just ended with structured shooting drills, to the accompaniment of Al Green's music, when Metta World Peace rushed out a back door. He was on a mission. Racing upstairs, along familiar paths, he headed straight for the offices of Donnie Walsh and Larry Bird. After a few minutes of how-are-you-good-to-see-you greetings and casual small talk, he returned to rejoin his Laker teammates.
